The paper proposes a set of indices to evaluate the quality of research produced by an author, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR), data mining (cs.DL), cybersecurity (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper specifically mentions the use of these indices in the field of computer science, which further supports these sub-categories. Among these sub-categories, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely as they are directly related to research evaluation and citation analysis.
